item.title: Need Pro Help Desperatly
item.dc:creator: @TeleNubby TeleNubby
item.description:
@TeleNubby wrote:

It’s the cache you’re using.

Go to C:/WINDOWS/ and delete the folder that’s labeled as .mpr_file_store_32

Now, go to http://moparisthebest.com and let the client load. Once it has loaded, an obvious thing has happened. It “re-installed” you’re cache that most clients use.

The problem was your cache was insufficient, or Silab’s client replaced it with files that normal clients couldn’t read because they were not edited for that reason. It might not have been Silab’s client, but that’s my only other guess. If it wasn’t any of the above, then you or some other program messed up your cache directory. But after you do what I told you to do, you should be fine.
